
cut-chunk:
   cut a chunk from image B that has the same aspect ratio as image A

cut-chunk --aspect A --offset P --scale B

  --aspect A : template image
  --offset P : number of pixels offset:
                 the cut image will be the full height of B, starting
                 from X position P on the left, or the full width of
                 B, starting from Y position P on top
  --scale : scale the output to be the same size as B

